<%#
  # Partial: _page.html.erb
  # Date: 11/20/2025
  # Author: MoisÃ©s Reis
  # Package: Kaminari
  #
  # Description: Renders a numbered link corresponding to a specific page number in the collection.
  #              It dynamically styles the element to highlight the current page versus other navigable pages.
  #
  # Usage: - What: Renders an individual, numbered link corresponding to a specific page
  #                in the paginated sequence. This link is the primary control for
  #                jumping between pages.
  #        - How: Uses dynamic classes to style the element: `button-secondary` when
  #               `page.current?` is true (active page) and `button-ghost` when false.
  #               The Kaminari `link_to_unless` helper displays the page number and
  #               disables the link when it's the current page.
  #        - Why: Provides the central navigational element of the pagination controls,
  #               enabling users to easily access any page in the collection.
  %>
<span class="button button-small rounded-[6px] <%= 'button-ghost' if !page.current? %> <%= 'button-secondary' if page.current? %>">
  <%= link_to_unless page.current?, page, url, {remote: remote, rel: page.rel} %>
</span>
